# Agent orientation

**Always read `AGENTS.md` at the repo root before starting any task.**

It contains the full project structure, the Overleaf deploy workflow, npm/test conventions, and the list of cursor rules.

## Key facts

- **Dual-purpose repo:** Astro static site (`src/`) + LaTeX question bank (`public/tex/`).
- **`.tex` files are the day-to-day editing surface.** Brand-new topics are imported from Overleaf via `npm run deploy-overleaf` (`scripts/deploy-from-overleaf.mjs`), which clones, compiles, places, and stages an entry in `data/resources-pending.json` for the splicer. Once a topic exists under `public/tex/`, edits happen in-repo: edit the QBT `.tex` (source of truth for question statements), run `npm run sync-questions` to propagate statement changes into the matching soln `.tex`, then rebuild PDFs with `npm run compile-tex -- <scope> --deploy` and commit `.tex` + `.pdf` together. CI does not run `latexmk` — whatever `.pdf` is committed ships.
- **Shell:** PowerShell (`pwsh`). Chain commands with `;` not `&&`. Use `Select-Object -First N` not `head`, `Select-String` (or `rg`) not `grep`, `Get-Content` not `cat`.
- **Build artefacts:** `public/tex/**/build/` (PDFs and aux files) — gitignored, never edit.
- **Generated TS:** `src/data/questionCounts.generated.ts` and `src/data/fileHashes.generated.ts` — regenerated by `scripts/count-questions.mjs` and `scripts/hash-assets.mjs` on every `predev`/`prebuild`/`precheck`. Never hand-edit.
- **Pre-commit:** runs `npx vitest run`, then `node scripts/check-tex.mjs`, then `node scripts/check-questions.mjs`. All three must pass.
- **Cursor rules:** `tex-bank.mdc` activates under `public/tex/**/*.tex`; `scripts.mdc` activates under `scripts/**/*.mjs`. Update them in lockstep with `AGENTS.md` whenever the underlying convention changes.
